Installing FastAPI

Step 1: Create a Project Folder
mkdir fastapi_course_app
cd fastapi_course_app
Step 2: Create a Virtual Environment
Windows
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
macOS or Linux
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Step 3: Install FastAPI
The current FastAPI tutorial recommends installing FastAPI with its standard optional dependencies:
            pip install "fastapi[standard]"
This installation includes the compcal development and server execution. A minimal installation can also be performed with pip install fastapi, but additional packages may then need to be installed separately.

Step 4: Verify the Installation
fastapi --version
You can also verify the Python import:
import fastapi
print("FastAPI imported successfully.")
Step 5: Create folder
fastapi_course_app
> cd fastapi_course_app
Step 6: Create requirements.txt
pip freeze > requirements.txt
A simple requirements file may contain packages such as:
fastapi
uvicorn
pydantic
The exact versions depend on the environment in which the file was created.




For a simple application:
fastapi_course_app/
├── main.py
├── requirements.txt
├── tests/
            └── test_main.py
For a larger application:
fastapi_course_app/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── main.py
│   ├── models.py / schemas.py / database.py
│   ├── dependencies.py
│   └── routers/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── courses.py / users.py
├── tests/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   └── test_courses.py
│ provides `APIRouter` for grouping related endpoints and organizing larger applications across multiple files. 
It is broadly comparable to Flask Blueprints. 




